This article emphasizes the importance of military justice in maintaining order and discipline within the armed forces. It states that each military justice case should be resolved based on its own facts, and the President expects all military personnel involved in the process to use their independent professional judgment in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. The article also highlights that there are no predetermined dispositions, outcomes, or sentences in military justice cases, as they are determined based on the individual facts and merits of each case and the application of due process by officials exercising their independent judgment.